# validatefx Provider

The validatefx provider offers reusable validation helpers that integrate with Terraform
configs. Each function returns a boolean allowing you to guard variables, locals, and
module inputs with familiar Terraform logic.

## Example Usage

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    validatefx = {
      source  = "The-DevOps-Daily/validatefx"
      version = "~> 0.1"
    }
  }
}

provider "validatefx" {}

locals {
  email_is_valid = provider::validatefx::email("alice@example.com")
  enforce_semver = provider::validatefx::assert(
    provider::validatefx::semver(var.release_version),
    "release_version must follow SemVer",
  )
}
```

